<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>

<chapter xml:id="ch-season1" xmlns:xi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XInclude">
  <title>Season 1: Mathematical Operations</title>

  <introduction>
    <p> When we are working with numbers, there are five types of calculations ("operations") we perform 
      <ul>
        <li>
          <p>
            Addition
          </p>
        </li>
        <li>
          <p>
            Subtraction
          </p>
        </li>
        <li>
          <p>
          Multiplication
          </p>
        </li>
        <li>
          <p>
            Division
          </p>
        </li>
        <li>
          <p>
            Exponentiation
          </p>
        </li>
      </ul>
      </p>
      <p>
      In this season, we will talk about the real-world situations where each of these operations is used, the symbols that are used to represent each operation,
      and the words that are used to indicate each operation.</p>
      <p>
      In problems where we need to perform multiple operations, we will learn the rules for the order of those operations (PEMDAS).
      </p>
  </introduction>
